A terror attack in Jaipur, India, killed 80 and injured 200, prompting global condemnation.
British and French officials expressed solidarity with India in combating terrorism.
The bombings, attributed to Islamic militants, reignited fears of Hindu-Muslim violence.
The US also denounced the attacks, standing with India in the fight against terrorism.
Two suspects were arrested, and heightened security measures were implemented nationwide.
The tragic event underscored the ongoing threat of terrorism in India, with past attacks claiming hundreds of lives.
The international community rallied behind India, offering support in the face of senseless violence.
